Events
------

sfEasyAuth will notify various events during its execution. Below is a list of the events
that it will notify, along with the event types and parameters passed.

All events are in the `sf_easy_auth` namespace. Event names should be self explanatory as
to when they events are triggered - but check the code if you need to.

Event name                            type        parameters                      Notes        
  pre_authentication                  notify      username, password              Called before a user's username and password are checked
  post_authentication                 notify      result                          True if a username & password are valid 
                                                                                  and the user is allowed to log in
  filter_login_redirect_url          filter      user. url                        User is the sf_user to log out, url is the
                                                                                  url they will be redirected to. All filters must
                                                                                  return the url, even if they don't modify it
  pre_logout                          notify      user                            User is the sf_user to log out
  filter_logout_redirect_url          filter      user. url                       User is the sf_user to log out, url is the
                                                                                  url they will be redirected to. All filters must
                                                                                  return the url, even if they don't modify it
  pre_password_reset_message          notify      user                            The sfEasyAuthUser to send a password reset email to
  pre_password_reset_resend_message   notify      user                            The sfEasyAuthUser to send a password reset email to. This event
                                                                                  is triggered when a user clicks on an expired password reset link.
  post_password_reset                 notify      user, password                  The sfEasyAuthUser to update the password of, and the password. This
                                                                                  event is triggered after a user's password has been updated.
  email_confirmed                     notify      user                            The sfEasyAuthUser who has just confirmed their email address.
  account_temporarily_locked          notify      user                            The sfEasyAuthUser whose account has just been temporarily locked.